          <h2>Facts about Sundar</h2>

          <p>
            <strong>Early Life :</strong> Sundar Pichai was born on July 12, 1972, in Chennai, India, as Pichai Sundararajan.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Academic Excellence:</strong> He holds a Bachelor's degree in Metallurgical Engineering from the Indian Institute of Technology (IIT) Kharagpur. He later earned a Master's degree in Material Sciences and Engineering from Stanford University and an MBA from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania.
          </p>

          <p>
           <strong>Google Journey:</strong> Sundar joined Google in 2004 and played a significant role in the development of popular products like Google Chrome and Chrome OS.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Android Leadership:</strong> He later led the development of Android, Google's mobile operating system, making it one of the most widely used platforms globally.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>CEO of Google:</strong> Sundar Pichai was appointed CEO of Google in August 2015 when Google underwent a major restructuring and became a subsidiary of Alphabet Inc. He became CEO of Alphabet Inc. in December 2019, overseeing the conglomerate's various businesses.
          </p>

          <p>
           <strong>Innovation Advocate:</strong> Pichai has been an advocate for innovation and artificial intelligence, emphasizing the importance of machine learning and AI in the future of technology.
          </p>
          <p>
